  "prompt": "How much should I charge for a commissioned piece of art?",
  "response": "Pricing art can depend on several factors:\n\n1. Your experience level\n- Beginner: $20-$50 per hour\n- Intermediate: $50-$150 per hour\n- Professional: $150-$500+ per hour\n\n2. Artwork complexity\n- Simple sketch: $50-$200\n- Detailed drawing: $200-$500\n- Complex piece: $500-$2,000+\n\n3. Materials used\n- Digital art: Often less expensive\n- Traditional media: May cost more due to supplies\n\n4. Size and time required\n- Smaller pieces: Lower price\n- Larger or more intricate works: Higher price\n\n5. Your reputation and portfolio\n- More established artists can charge more\n\nSuggestions:\n- Calculate your hourly rate\n- Estimate total hours needed\n- Add cost of materials\n- Consider market rates for similar work\n- Factor in your skill level and demand\n\nUltimately, pricing is flexible and depends on your specific situation. Consider researching similar artists in your style and market.\n\nWould you like help calculating a specific price for your artwork?",
